FIRST NATIONAL BANK OF SANTA ANA v. E. A. LYNCH, as Trustee in Bankruptcy of the Estate of Grey M. Skidmore, Bankrupt. No. 9143. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 27, 1939. Horton & Horton, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Raphael Dechter and George T. Gog-gin, both of Los Angeles, Cal., for appel-lee.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, ‘ and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal in this cause dismissed, that a decree be filed and entered pursuant to stipulation, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
